<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 02 at 4:25AM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...WIDESPREAD LIGHT SNOW CONTINUES THIS MORNING...
A slight uptick in snowfall intensity has been observed generally
north of M59, where snowfall rates around a quarter inch per hour
will be likely, and up to a half-inch per hour will be possible.
These better snowfall rates will start to fill in across the M59
corridor this morning. Reductions in visibilities with this
snowfall is expected as untreated roadways remain snow covered.
Drivers are urged to exercise caution and take it slow this
morning.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
